    "prerequisites": ["time-matrix-13"],
    "lesson_content_markdown": "# The Deep Past: Past Perfect\n\nSometimes we talk about the past, but then we want to talk about something that happened even **earlier**. We call this the \"Deep Past\" or the **Past Perfect**.\n\n### 1. The Timeline\nImagine two events in the past:\n1.  **Event 1 (Deep Past)**: I ate breakfast.\n2.  **Event 2 (Past)**: I went to class.\n\nTo show that breakfast happened first, we say: \n- *\"I **had eaten** breakfast before I **went** to class.\"*\n\n### 2. How to Make It\nUse **had** + the **Past Participle** (V3).\n\n- **Formula**: Subject + had + V3 (e.g., done, finished, seen)\n- **Example**: By the time the professor arrived, the students **had already finished** their talk.\n\n### 3. Common Keywords\n- **Before**: I had finished studying **before** my friends called.\n- **By the time**: **By the time** we reached the library, it **had closed**.\n- **Already**: They **had already lived** there when the fire started.\n\n### 4. Why use it?\nIt helps make the order of your story clear when you are already talking about the past.\n\n---",
